<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-126287" number="113719" version="1724">
			<HEADING>Chapter 13: Changes to Burial Claims</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16912" name="T68C013"/>Chapter 13: Changes to Burial Claims</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-126289" number="113720" version="1724">
								<HEADING>§ 13-01 Changes to Burial Claims Generally.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16914" name="T68C013_13-01"/>§ 13-01 Changes to Burial Claims Generally.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126291" number="113721" version="1724">
									<PARA>Notwithstanding any provision of 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK> to the contrary, the following provisions shall apply all applications for an HRA burial allowance: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126975" number="113722" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Notwithstanding the provisions of 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK>, the allowance provided for in 68 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C013_13-02" destination-id="0-0-0-16938">13-02</LINK>, or in 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK>, as applicable, shall not be available where the total burial expenses, as defined in 68 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002_2-02" destination-id="0-0-0-13345">2-02</LINK>, exceed $3,400. In determining whether such $3,400 cap has been exceeded, the following costs will be disregarded: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126974" number="113723" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>the cost of cremation or the burial plot and grave opening; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126973" number="113724" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any costs charged by a funeral director that are related to the disinterment of a body that was buried on or after March 12, 2020 on Hart Island. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126972" number="113725" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The time within which any person may submit an application for a burial allowance is increased from sixty (60) days to one hundred and twenty (120) days from the date of death. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126971" number="113726" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Anyone who is eligible for an allowance for burial expenses or under this section or under 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK>, as applicable, may apply for such expenses either prior to or after burial or cremation. The requirement in 68 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002_2-09" destination-id="0-0-0-13359">2-09</LINK>(d) that DSS/HRA must decide any applications made prior to burial or cremation within two business days is suspended. However, DSS/HRA will make decisions on all applications within a reasonable time. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126970" number="113727" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Applications under this section or under 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK>, as applicable, need not be made in person and may be made online, by email, by fax and by any other remote means as DSS/HRA may designate. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126969" number="113728" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>In determining the amount of the allowance, the value of any resources or income that are not liquid or available at the time of the decedent&apos;s death and not available at the time of application shall not be deducted. However, DSS/HRA reserves the right to recover against any such resources consistent with State law. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126968" number="113729" version="1724">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(f)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The provisions of 68 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002_2-09" destination-id="0-0-0-13359">2-09</LINK>(b)(ii), prohibiting an allowance for veteran burials that occur in private cemeteries other than Calverton Cemetery, are suspended. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126301" number="113730" version="1724">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/31/2020, eff. 8/30/2020) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-052]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-126967" number="113731" version="1999">
								<HEADING>§ 13-02 Increase in Burial Allowance.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16938" name="T68C013_13-02"/>§ 13-02 Increase in Burial Allowance.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126977" number="113732" version="1999">
									<PARA>Notwithstanding any provision of 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK> to the contrary, the allowance for burial expenses described in 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK> that are payable by DSS/HRA is $1,700. This allowance can be used towards burial expenses, as defined in 68 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C002" destination-id="0-0-0-13341">Chapter 2</LINK>, including the costs set forth in paragraphs (1) and (2) of subdivision (a) of 68 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T68C013_13-01" destination-id="0-0-0-16914">13-01</LINK> that are disregarded in determining the cap set forth in such subdivision. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-063]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-126302" number="113733" version="1999">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/31/2020, eff. 8/30/2020; amended City Record 12/1/2020, eff. 12/31/2020; amended City Record 6/1/2021, eff. 7/1/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-063]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>